In mathematics, in the theory of finite groups, a '''Brauer tree''' is a [[Tree (graph theory)|tree]] that encodes the [[Character (group theory)|characters]] of a [[Block (representation theory)|block]] with [[cyclic group|cyclic]] [[defect group]] of a [[finite group]].  In fact, the trees encode the [[group algebra]] up to [[Morita equivalence]].  Such algebras coming from Brauer trees are called Brauer tree algebras.

{{harvtxt|Feit|1984}} described the possibilities for Brauer trees.

